gram\": \"Pioneer Day\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cox, who wouldsign the host agreementwith the IOC on behalf of the state, said bringing another Olympics to Utah after first hosting in2002could serve as a catalyst for determining where best to invest tax dollars at all levels of government.\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 553, \"end\": 556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.812993675257156e-13, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 615, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999988052739215, \"rank\": 1.1947273861629209e-06, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cox\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"the host\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 534}, {\"ngram\": \"behalf\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 566}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"another Olympics\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"a catalyst\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 671}, {\"ngram\": \"tax dollars\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"all levels\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 734}, {\"ngram\": \"government\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We obviously want to maintain our quality of life while focusing on economic growth and prosperity.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 851, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our quality\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 793}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 801}, {\"ngram\": \"economic growth\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 835}, {\"ngram\": \"prosperity\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think that goes without saying,\\\" the governor said, adding at the end of the meeting, \\\"We have this just extra motivation that we need to stay relevant and get this right.\\\"\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 1026, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the governor\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 923}, {\"ngram\": \"the meeting\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 938}, {\"ngram\": \"this just extra motivation\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 975}, {\"ngram\": \"this right\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transportation projects were mentioned multiple times.\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1082, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Transportation projects\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Utah House Speaker Mike Schultz, R-Hooper, said for the 2002 Winter Games, \\\"we came together andgot ahead of it,\\\" expanding I-15 and opening the Utah Transit Authority's initial TRAX light rail lines.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1083, \"end\": 1087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999988052739215, \"rank\": 1.1947273861629209e-06, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}, {\"begin\": 1088, \"end\": 1101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7341806953741683e-13, \"text\": \"House Speaker\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\"}, {\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Schultz_(2000s_pitcher)\", \"score\": 0.6157332245838193, \"rank\": 0.36842105263166286, \"text\": \"Mike Schultz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Schultz_(2000s_pitcher)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Schultz_(2000s_pitcher)\"}, {\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah_Transit_Authority\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Utah Transit Authority\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah_Transit_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah_Transit_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"R-Hooper\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1124}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2002 Winter Games\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1156}, {\"ngram\": \"I-15\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We need to identify what that looks like today, working toward getting that done which will have a huge benefit well after the Olympics,\\\" Schultz said, noting while Utah \\\"has done a great job at meeting our needs for transportation, (it's) certainly not perfect.\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1451, \"end\": 1455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999988052739215, \"rank\": 1.1947273861629209e-06, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"today\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge benefit\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1397}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1421}, {\"ngram\": \"Schultz\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"a great job\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1477}, {\"ngram\": \"our needs\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \"transportation\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are some areas where we are a little bit behind.\\\"\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1604, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some areas\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1569}]}, {\"sentence\": 